### `.harness/knowledge/conventions.md`
```markdown
# Conventions — Google Style + 阿里巴巴开发手册 + Cloud-Native

> Provenance
> - Authoritative paradigm: Google Style Guides + Alibaba Java Development Manual + 12-Factor / Cloud-Native + Chris Richardson's microservices patterns — the union covers code style through distributed concerns
> - Investigation protocol: sample `git churn` hotspots and incident history; every convention must be backed by an in-repo `path:line` example and a citation to its industry source; evidence-or-silence; tool-enforceable rules link to tool config rather than duplicating prose
> - Output form: one section per concern — Project practice + Industry paradigm + canonical `path:line` + GOOD / BAD pair; mandatory sections include concurrency / transactions / distributed locks (with fencing-token caveat) / caching / MQ / middleware / config / API / observability / security

## Code Style & Naming
- Project practice: ⟨…⟩
- Industry paradigm: ⟨e.g. Google Java Style §5⟩
- Canonical example: ⟨path:line⟩
- GOOD: ⟨snippet⟩ · BAD: ⟨snippet⟩

## Error Handling
- Project practice: ⟨…⟩  · Industry: 阿里 §异常日志
- GOOD / BAD · path:line

## Logging
- Project practice: ⟨structured logger · request_id · level policy⟩
- Industry: 12-Factor §XI Logs
- GOOD / BAD · path:line

## Testing
- Project practice: ⟨pyramid / contract / golden tests⟩
- Industry: Google Testing on the Toilet · 阿里 §单元测试
- GOOD / BAD · path:line

## Concurrency & Locks
- Project practice: ⟨thread / coroutine model · shared-state policy⟩
- Industry: 阿里 §并发处理 · Java Concurrency in Practice
- Pitfalls: deadlock order · livelock · false-sharing
